UID:fWaGIc8r5K3d9Uj7oIS7G
SUMMARY:Free Tax Help
DTSTAMP:20260325T062329Z
DTSTART:20260325T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Wednesday\, March 25\, 2026\, 10am - 1:30pm\n\nTrained voluntee
	rs will be available to answer questions and prepare personal tax returns.
	\n\nLocation Link:\n\nBroadview Branch\n\nRoom Location: Meeting Room\n\nR
	egistration Required: Registration is not required.\n\nDetailed Descriptio
	n: This service is free and available to individuals only. The free servic
	e is not available for business tax returns. To receive tax help\, bring t
	he following documents:\,\n\nRequired:\n\nPhoto identification\, Social Se
	curity cards or Individual Taxpayer Identification Numbers \\(ITIN\\) for 
	everyone listed on the tax return.\, Proof of income\, for example\, W2s a
	nd 1099s \\(Social Security benefits\\)\, Official documents on Social Sec
	urity Administration letterhead\, Medicare card \\(if Social Security numb
	er is followed by an "A"\\)\, Be prepared to provide information about hea
	lth care coverage for each person on the return.\,\n\nRecommended:\n\nLast
	 year&'s tax return\, if available\, Bank account and routing numbers for 
	direct deposit of refunds\, Photocopies or computer print-outs of any of t
	hese documents willbe accepted.\, Due to federal budget cuts the IRS is un
	able to provide the Library with certain tax forms and instruction booklet
	s.\, Most IRS forms are available online at\n\nwww.irs.gov .\, You may mak
	e free black-and-white prints of the forms from Library computers:\n\nwww.
	spl.org/Print \, Thanks to our partner\n\nAARP .\n\nEvent Logistics: AARP 
	Tax Help locations serve anyone who earned less than $80\,000 in 2025.\, F
	or eligibility details\, contact AARP at 888-227-7669.\n\nContact Us: If y
	ou have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\
	nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for people with disabil
	ities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days befo
	re the event to request accommodations.\, All Library programs are free an
	d open to the public.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/fre
	e-tax-help/18162991/2026-03-25T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Learning & Education
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/20
	26-03-25T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-learning
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Learning & Education
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H30M
END:VEVENT
