BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:PyK6-yKPtFJT0g-HgVOaZ
SUMMARY:Free Tax Help
DTSTAMP:20260325T062329Z
DTSTART:20260325T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Wednesday\, March 25\, 2026\, 12:30 - 6:30pm\n\nTrained volunte
	ers will be available to answer questions and prepare personal tax returns
	.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nCentral Library\n\nRoom Location: Level 5 - Mixing 
	Chamber Meeting Room\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not require
	d.\n\nDetailed Description: This service is free and available to individu
	als only. The free service is not available for business tax returns.\, To
	 receive tax help\, bring the following documents:\,\n\nRequired:\n\nPhoto
	 identification\, Social Security cards or Individual Taxpayer Identificat
	ion Numbers \\(ITIN\\) for everyone listed on the tax return\, Proof of in
	come\, for example\, W2s and 1099s \\(Social Security benefits\\)\, Offici
	al documents on Social Security Administration letterhead\, Medicare card 
	\\(if Social Security number is followed by an "A"\\)\, Be prepared to pro
	vide information about health care coverage for each person on the return\
	,\n\nRecommended:\n\nLast year&'s tax return\, if available\, Bank account
	 and routing numbers for direct deposit of refunds\, Photocopies or comput
	er print-outs of any of these documents will be accepted.\, Due to federal
	 budget cuts the IRS is unable to provide the Library with certain tax for
	ms and instruction booklets.\, Most IRS forms are available online at\n\nw
	ww.irs.gov. \, You may make free black-and-white prints of the forms from 
	Library computers:\n\nwww.spl.org/Print \, Thanks to our partner\n\nUnited
	 Way of King County .\n\nEvent Logistics: United Way Tax Help locations se
	rve anyone who earned less than $80\,000 in 2025 \\(or less than $96\,000 
	for non-single filers\\).\, For eligibility details\, contact United Way a
	t 206-461-3700.\n\nContact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\
	nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide acc
	ommodations for people with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncont
	actLEAP\n\nat least seven days before the event to request accommodations.
	\, All Library programs are free and open to the public.\,\n\nhttps://seat
	oday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/2026-03-25T00\n\n
	From SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/20
	26-03-25T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
