BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:yGD3wQR1AZz-UoUYNGqL0
SUMMARY:Beyond Mysticism: The Modern Northwest
DTSTAMP:20260325T062331Z
DTSTART:20260401T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:image: Drift No. 2\, 1936\, Malcolm M. Roberts\, American\, 191
	3-1990\, tempera on board\, 25 1/2 x 20 5/8 in.\, Seattle Art Museum\, Eug
	ene Fuller Memorial Collection\, 37.103\, © Malcolm M. Roberts\, photo: Sc
	ott Leen.\n\nInspired by the region’s natural beauty and rapidly changing 
	city\, this exhibition showcases artists who told the raw story of Seattle
	 in the 20th century. By sharing the Pacific Northwest’s perspective throu
	gh trending art styles—including Social Realism\, Surrealism\, and Abstrac
	t Expressionism—these artists offered a unique take on Modernist art and c
	hallenged the “mystic” label ascribed to their works.\n\nSpearheading the 
	movement were local icons Mark Tobey\, Kenneth Callahan\, Guy Anderson\, a
	nd Morris Graves—but the range and breadth of Pacific Northwest art goes b
	eyond the “Big Four” of the Northwest School. Featuring more than 150 piec
	es\, this exhibition showcases works that investigate the complexities of 
	daily life in the region. Whether applying an ecocritical lens or producin
	g dreamy and uncanny visuals\, these artists expressed the duality of the 
	natural world and city life to warn of the environmental and social impact
	s of industrialization.\n\nFrom Malcolm Roberts to Kenjiro Nomura\, learn 
	how Northwest artists applied their regional perspective to broader artist
	ic developments to create a new form of American Modernism.\n\nThe exhibit
	ion is accompanied by a fully illustrated catalogue authored by Theresa Pa
	panikolas\, SAM’s Ann M. Barwick Curator of American Art.\n\nhttps://seato
	day.6amcity.com/events/#/details/beyond-mysticism-the-modern-northwest/183
	08126/2026-04-01T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/beyond-mysticism-the-mode
	rn-northwest/18308126/2026-04-01T00
LOCATION:Seattle Art Museum\, 1300 First Avenue\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:1Xm1hZOOd2GvtTttPaq6Z
SUMMARY:March Madness Watch Party at Five Iron Golf - Seattle Capitol Hill
DTSTAMP:20260325T062331Z
DTSTART:20260401T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Five Iron Golf is your College Basketball HQ this March! Gather
	 your crew and book 1–2 simulator bays for up to 12 people \\(6 people per
	 bay\\) for a bracket-busting watch party experience. Enjoy all-day TV cov
	erage of college basketball alongside cutting-edge golf and multisport sim
	ulators\, a locally-inspired menu\, and custom beverage packages.\n\nBook 
	your watch party for March 19 or 20 and you'll automatically be entered to
	 win a 20-person happy hour with drinks and appetizers — a $1\,000 value!\
	n\nGroup packages can include reserved event space\, team-specific décor\,
	 a dedicated staff member\, full-screen and/or picture-in-picture viewing\
	, a customizable menu\, beverage packages\, free club rentals\, multisport
	 simulators\, and table games. Select the "Small Event" option at booking 
	to ensure simulator bays are placed side-by-side. Availability of select f
	eatures varies by location.\n\nPromotions:\n\nHappy Hour – "It's 5i o'Cloc
	k Somewhere" \\(Monday–Friday\, 3–6 PM\\)\n\nEnjoy $5 bottomless boneless 
	wings\, $10 bottomless bone-in wings\, $5 select beers/cans/cocktails\, $5
	 dips \\(guacamole\, hot honey ricotta\, hummus\\)\, half-off pizzas\, and
	 $5 featured shots. Dine-in only at participating locations\; simulator re
	ntal may be required.\n\n5i After Dark – "Swing In\, For Less"  \\(Sunday–
	Thursday 9 PM to close | Friday–Saturday 10 PM to close\\)\n\nFeatures $29
	/hr simulator rentals plus the same great food and drink specials as Happy
	 Hour\, with wings priced per dozen rather than bottomless. Dine-in only a
	t participating locations\; simulator rental may be required.\n\nhttps://s
	eatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/march-madness-watch-party-at-five-iro
	n-golf-seattle-capitol-hill/18268907/2026-04-01T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All 
	Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/march-madness-watch-party
	-at-five-iron-golf-seattle-capitol-hill/18268907/2026-04-01T00
LOCATION:Five Iron Golf - Seattle Capitol Hill\, 1525 11th Ave Suite 100\, 
	Seattle\, WA
